# Sample .stignore — copy this file to <your --source folder>/.stignore and
# edit as needed. See "Ignoring source files" in README.md for the full rules.
#
# One gitignore-style glob pattern per line. Blank lines and lines starting
# with "#" are skipped.
#
# Matching rules (see Sync/IgnoreRules.cs):
#   - A pattern with NO "/" matches a file by NAME, at any depth in the tree.
#   - A pattern WITH a "/" is matched against the whole source-relative path.
#   - "*"  matches any run of characters EXCEPT "/" (stays within one folder).
#   - "**" matches any run of characters INCLUDING "/" (crosses folders).
#   - "?"  matches a single non-"/" character.
#   - Matching is case-insensitive. There is no negation ("!pattern") and no
#     directory-only "/" suffix — this is not a full .gitignore implementation.

# --- Ignore one specific file, anywhere in the tree ---
FB_Scratch.st

# --- Ignore every file matching a name pattern, anywhere in the tree ---
*_deprecated.st
*_old.st

# --- Ignore an ENTIRE FOLDER (and everything nested under it) ---
# The trailing "/**" is required — a bare folder name (e.g. just "Legacy")
# only matches a FILE named "Legacy", not a folder.
Lib/Legacy/**

# --- Ignore one folder's direct files but NOT its subfolders ---
# ("*" does not cross "/", so this leaves Lib/WorkInProgress/Sub/*.st alone)
Lib/WorkInProgress/*.st

# --- Ignore a folder at any depth in the tree (not just at the root) ---
# Because there's a "/", this is path-anchored from the source root, so it
# would NOT match a "Generated" folder that isn't directly under Lib/ —
# use "**/Generated/**" if you want it to match at any depth instead.
Lib/Generated/**
**/Generated/**
